Center Fundraiser.

03:44.057 --> 03:46.646
<i>And I'm really looking</i>
<i>forward to the performance.</i>

03:47.004 --> 03:49.564
But I'll be watching
safely from the audience.

03:50.336 --> 03:54.288
Well, I think it's a terrible
waste of an exquisite talent,

03:54.752 --> 03:56.563
but I understand that
you're not comfortable.

03:57.312 --> 03:57.993
Thank you.

03:58.675 --> 03:59.881
Ooh! Angel's right!

04:00.048 --> 04:00.995
We better get going!

04:01.232 --> 04:03.817
There's a lot of work to
do before tomorrow's event!

04:16.499 --> 04:17.318
Ahem!

04:17.392 --> 04:20.713
All right, Pony Tones, let's
run through that again!

04:31.366 --> 04:35.228
♪ Everypony's saying you should
<i>learn to express your voice. ♪</i>

04:35.235 --> 04:38.336
<i>♪ But if talk doesn't seem</i>
<i>like it's the answer ♪</i>

04:38.441 --> 04:40.099
<i>♪ luckily you have a choice. </i>

04:40.204 --> 04:45.344
<i>♪ When you find you've got the</i>
<i>music, got the music in you. ♪</i>

04:45.395 --> 04:49.808
<i>♪ Find you've got the music</i>
<i>got the music in you. ♪</i>

04:53.020 --> 04:54.451
Whoo hoo! Yeah!

04:54.678 --> 04:56.265
Rarity, you were awesome!

04:57.148 --> 05:00.230
Thank you, Spike, but
this is an ensemble.

05:02.118 --> 05:04.249
Enh, the rest of you
were pretty good, too.

05:04.950 --> 05:08.240
Oh, I thought you were all
amazing, Pony Tones.

05:08.633 --> 05:09.804
Thanks, Fluttershy!

05:10.281 --> 05:12.800
Now, Pony Tones, I want you
all to rest your voices

05:12.828 --> 05:13.843
for the remainder of the day.

05:14.041 --> 05:16.326
We'll do a final run-through
tomorrow before the big event.

05:16.480 --> 05:17.075
All right?

05:17.344 --> 05:17.897
